# Backend API Keys Configuration

**Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your actual API keys**

```bash
# Firebase Admin SDK
# Get from: https://console.firebase.google.com/project/YOUR_PROJECT/settings/serviceaccounts/adminsdk
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=gamesdev-factory
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=your-service-account@projects.iam.gserviceaccount.com
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYOUR_KEY_HERE\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

# Google Play Console API
# Get from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
GOOGLE_PLAY_PACKAGE_NAME=com.afonso.fxtrade.gamesdev
GOOGLE_PLAY_CLIENT_EMAIL=your-api@developer.gserviceaccount.com
GOOGLE_PLAY_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYOUR_KEY_HERE\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

# AdMob API
# Get from: https://admob.google.com
ADMOB_ACCOUNT_ID=pub-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Facebook Ads API
# Get from: https://developers.facebook.com/apps
FACEBOOK_ACCESS_TOKEN=EAAB...

# Google Ads API
# Get from: https://ads.google.com
GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Server Configuration
PORT=3001
NODE_ENV=production

# Dashboard Configuration
DASHBOARD_URL=https://gamesdev-dashboard.vercel.app
ALERT_EMAIL=afonso@email.com
ALERT_PHONE=+5511999999999
ALERT_TELEGRAM=@afonso

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info
```

---

## 🔑 How to Get API Keys

### Firebase Admin SDK

1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com
2. Select your project (or create new: `gamesdev-factory`)
3. Go to Settings → Service Accounts
4. Click "Generate new private key"
5. Download JSON file
6. Extract values:
   - `project_id` → FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID
   - `client_email` → FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL
   - `private_key` → FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY

### Google Play Console API

1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com
2. Create new project or select existing
3. Enable "Google Play Android Developer API"
4. Go to APIs & Services → Credentials
5. Create Service Account
6. Download JSON key
7. Extract values similar to Firebase

### AdMob API

1. Go to https://admob.google.com
2. Go to Account → Settings
3. Copy Account ID (pub-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx)

### Facebook Ads API

1. Go to https://developers.facebook.com/apps
2. Create app or select existing
3. Go to Tools → Graph API Explorer
4. Generate access token with permissions:
   - ads_read
   - ads_management

### Google Ads API

1. Go to https://ads.google.com
2. Go to Tools → API Center
3. Generate developer token
4. Create OAuth credentials

---

## 🚀 After Configuration

1. Copy this file: `cp .env.example .env`
2. Edit `.env` with your actual keys
3. Install dependencies: `npm install`
4. Start server: `npm start`
5. Test: `curl http://localhost:3001/health`

---

**Keep your `.env` file secure and never commit it to Git!** 🔒
